values:
&nbsp;Ok.

I am hoping this is the calm after the storm. I'm feeling better. Could easily blame everything on girly hormones but I think I was justified in my upset. I filled up labor day weekend with hardcore college fun...

Friday night&nbsp;- drove to berkely, got sexy and fucked up on absinthe with allie, smoked bowls in bart, rode out to the city and partied until the bars closed. Our timing couldn't have been better... it was a warm night in SF, the Bart was open all night because of bay bridge construction, and everybody was out partying in full force this labor day weekend. The bartride home was ridiculously packed... we really were sardines...&nbsp; stole a cab from in front of dozens of angry oaklanders... got back to allies and got hiiiiigh in the garage.&nbsp;

Saturday - woke up sans hangover, thanks to belvedere vodka tonics at all the bars. Smoked, had AMAZING food, went swimming at the Claremont. very swanky. Drove home, spent a couple hours there, then drove to Nate's for drinking and party prep.

Sunday- spent the whole day at nate's, preparing for his dad's sixtieth bday party. Lots of prep in the morning... the party was really fantastic. It was huge. Most&nbsp;delicious potluck ever.&nbsp;Edwin, Thomas and Aaron were there too. Smoked too much, drank too much, ate too much... got WAY too much sun. Waged pool war with little children, snuck around the property smoking and drinking wine, fell a little harder for mr. poon.

had a fantastic first&nbsp; _____.

oh.

Monday- hung around. took it easy. went shooting. im such a good shot.&nbsp;me nad nate are a pair of NBKs. like bonnie and clyde. went to REI and found a camel pack on sale for $65... bought it... aaaand tomorrow, is nates birthday.&nbsp;

but man im wiped. and i just got home to discover my parents have cleaned all the rugs / moved furnitue but i've got to move it back now and finish the walls in my bedroom. wheweee. i'll be nice and stoned while working at least .

i pretty much live out of my backpack these days. its a nice feeling. siiiiimple. life is sweet. im so enamored. scared still. the grass really is greener here, but i guess im worried about a dryspell... or getting kicked out of the pasture...&nbsp;
